# Linear Probing

## Overview
Linear probing resolves collisions in a hash table by checking the next available position until an empty slot is found. If the end of the table is reached, the search wraps around to the beginning.

## Efficiency
- Uses the **MOD** operator to calculate the initial address in constant time.
- Stops searching immediately once an empty slot or the required value is found, avoiding unnecessary comparisons.
- Wraps around to the beginning of the table, ensuring every location is checked before reporting that the table is full.
- Stores all data in a single array, so no additional memory is needed apart from the table itself.
